The script is added before the <style> tag and the rest of the content to ensure the page is hidden (with opacity: 0) before any flicker can occur.
This pre-hiding script adds a style element that sets the body’s opacity to 0. After 3 seconds, or when the CSS has loaded, it removes the style element, making the page visible.
No need to modify the existing HTML structure (i.e., no need for a <head> or <body> tag).
This approach keeps your code unchanged while preventing flickering effectively.
